{"id": "duc04-testb-22:2#8", "contents": "The arrest of Krstic has sparked a strong reaction from the Bosnian Serbs, who have threatened to reduce contacts with NATO-led peacekeeping forces to the \"necessary minimum.\" Nikola Poplasen, the hardline Bosnian Serb president, condemned the arrest, stating that it would harm the implementation of the Dayton agreement that ended the 1992-1995 Bosnian war. In contrast, NATO officials have praised the arrest, with Secretary-General Javier Solana warning that other war crimes suspects still at large \"should realize that they, too, will be brought to justice.\" The arrest brings the total number of people arrested for war crimes to nine."}
